This pass kept the correctness work from the in-progress rewrite, but replaced the slower warmed-cache formatter with a simpler split-cache layout: hot formatter tables are now normal_line_cache[width][num] and cursor_line_cache[width][num]. That removes the old per-number boolean subtable choice, avoids the warmed-line bookkeeping, and lets the render path collapse to one cache selection plus one fallback build.

Common widths 1..5 are seeded eagerly because they cover the typical <= 99,999 line case. Wider widths still work via on-demand cache creation, and rare large line numbers still memoize lazily. The update path keeps the more important behavioral fixes from the rewrite: clear stale statuscolumn values on excluded/invalid windows, iterate buffer windows through nvim_list_wins(), and store cursorline backup state on the target window instead of leaking through vim.w/current-window state.

